This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on August 23, 2016. The order is an amendment to Executive Order 13673, which is related to fair pay and safe workplaces. The amendment aims to promote economy and efficiency in procurement by contracting with responsible sources who comply with labor laws. The order specifies changes to subsections of Executive Order 13673, including the disclosure of information to a designated entity, the advice provided by the entity, and the submission of information to the entity. The order also includes general provisions, stating that it does not affect existing authorities or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It further clarifies that the order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States. The order is effective immediately and applies to all solicitations for contracts as set forth in any final rule issued by the Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council under this order and Executive Order 13673.